description:
"Kennedy" is a news panel show hosted by Kennedy Montgomery. Kennedy Montgomery is a libertarian that you may recognize from 90's MTV, Stossel, and the Independents.

Kennedy kicks the night off talking about the View & their comments about Fiorina. Apparently they're more concerned with the way Fiorina looks than her policy. Carely is supposed to go back on the show this Friday, so we'll see how that goes.

Tonight's party panel consists of JULIE ROSINSKY, JIMMY FAILLA, and MATT WELCH. They continue to talk about The View & Fiorina. (Also touching on if The View would ever say similar things about Clinton.) Paul Ryan is now the speaker of the House. Ted Cruz and Marco Rubio are running for president. Is the GOP trending younger for the first time ever? At a Meet the Press interview Jeb Bush acknowledged that his debate performance could have been better and that his campaign is sagging. Of course he cloaked the whole statement in smug arrogance.

Last week the White House announced that a small number of special operations forces were going to be deployed in Syria as part of the United State's anti-ISIS strategy. The special ops are supposed to be training moderates, not leading charges. But is it a good idea either way? DR. RON PAUL the consummate anti-war advocate is against it and here to detail why. He says there's no plan, no exit strategy, no entry strategy, and is escalating the situation. Afterwards they move on to the nomination of Speaker Ryan. Ron Paul thinks it'll be more of the same. 

Speaker of the House Paul Ryan recently gave an interview talking about the smell of his new office. Apparently Speaker Boehner had a nasty smoking habit. Tattoo popularity has sky rocketed. Unsurprisingly so has regret about getting said tattoos. Tiger Wood's long time caddy has released a memoir that details his time spent with Woods. Apparently he's a difficult boss. Quote, "It's like I was a slave." 

BRIAN BRENBERG of King's College is here to talk about 'the Debt Bomb.' Washington has recently passed a new budget. We're well on track to owing 19.5 trillion by the time Obama leaves office. Bush doubled the debt - now Obama has done it again. It's really a bipartisan issue.

Nightcap. Kennedy suits up to step onto the frontlines of the war against Christmas. It's November 2nd, and she's already hearing Christmas music. This makes Kennedy mad.
